Some voters in Sokoto state have expressed joy to exercise their voting right for the first time in their lives.
“We are happy to have reached the age of voting ,” declared an excited Hassana Muhammad flanked by four other first time voters. She said it was a memorable experience for them as they partook in choosing the leaders to rule the country in the next four years.
“We will use the opportunity to choose a credible candidates,” Hassana said. 2015: Voter cards, registration and fear of disenfranchisement FCT Elections: Vulnerable groups receive priority attention in Kwali Now that prisoners can vote